llama.cpp / ggml
----------------

Source: https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
Copyright (c) 2023-2026 The ggml authors
License: MIT

runNburn contains specific portions adapted or translated from llama.cpp and
ggml. Existing source comments identify the relevant ports and compatibility
references. Principal adapted portions include:

- Reference quantization helpers and GGML-compatible codebooks identified in
  `crates/rnb-cpu/src/quantize/`.
- The AVX2 quantized dot-product port in
  `crates/rnb-cpu/src/gemm/avx2_dot.rs`.
- CUDA compatibility tables and quantized-kernel portions whose source comments
  identify llama.cpp or ggml as their reference.
- The coalesced quantized GEMV kernels and gated-delta-net mapping in
  `crates/rnb-backend/metal/src/` that explicitly identify llama.cpp as their
  source or mapping reference.

This attribution applies only to the portions identified as adapted. Native
runNburn policies, APIs, data layouts, integration code, and independently
developed kernels are runNburn work. The llama.cpp/ggml-derived portions remain
under the MIT License below; runNburn modifications and original code are
provided under the Apache License, Version 2.0, unless a source file states
otherwise.

