KVarN
-----

Method and paper:
https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.03458

Official implementation:
https://github.com/huawei-csl/KVarN
Reference revision:
7586257f1c632e63187bfacbbe21ccb51540f7b3
License: Apache License, Version 2.0

runNburn's KVarN support is a runNburn-native Rust, CUDA, and Metal
implementation informed by the KVarN paper and checked against its official
Apache-2.0 reference backend. The CPU quantization module records
the exact reference revision it follows. The packed-record layout, backend API,
runtime policy, and CUDA/Metal fused decode kernels are runNburn-specific work.

Principal areas include:

- `crates/rnb-cpu/src/quantize/kvarn.rs`.
- `crates/rnb-llm/src/kv_cache/kvarn.rs`.
- `crates/rnb-runtime/src/policy/kvarn.rs`.
- `crates/rnb-backend/cuda/cuda/kernels/kvarn_attention.cuh`.
- `crates/rnb-backend/metal/src/kvarn_attention.metal`.

This attribution identifies the method and reference implementation; it does
not characterize the listed files as wholesale copies of upstream code.
runNburn's KVarN implementation is distributed under the Apache License,
Version 2.0, included in the repository `LICENSE` file.

KVarN paper authors:
Lorenz K. Muller, Philippe Bich, Chiara Boretti, Hyun-Min Chang,
Jiawei Zhuang, and Lukas Cavigelli.
